<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>Visio-B</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.2.1.min.js" integrity="sha256-hwg4gsxgFZhOsEEamdOYGBf13FyQuiTwlAQgxVSNgt4=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/normalize/5.0.0/normalize.css">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto+Condensed|Source+Sans+Pro" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="index.css" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>

<section>       

<!-- This section provides the first introduction for the name of the app: Visio as well as the introduction-->
<nav role="navigation">
  <header role="banner">
  <h1>Visio</h1> 
  </header>
</nav>

<main role="main">

<div class="openingBox">
  <p>We all have goals and aspirations in life, but how can we reach them? The purpose of this app is to help individuals organize their ideas to create clear short-term or longterm goals. Welcome to Visio!</p>
</div>
</section>

 <!-- This section contains the first form element used for signup or login-->  
<section class="sectionIndex">
<div class="signUpIn"> 

  <form role="form" class="formOpener js-login-form" action="#">
  <legend>Login or SignUp</legend>
  <label class="username" for="username">Username:
  <input id="username" title="Username" type="text" class="u-name"  placeholder="testu5@gmail.com" pattern="[a-z0-9._%+-]+@[a-z0-9.-]+\.[a-z]{2,4}$" required>
  </label>

  <label for="password">Password:
  <input id="password" title="Password"  type="password" class="p-word" placeholder="password05" required>
  </label>
          <p class="paraTag">Demo Username: testu5@gmail.com</p>
          <p class="paraTag">Demo Password: password05</p>

 <!-- If a client clicks the login button then the .logIn class function in public/index.js will run verfying the user and loading the pick-goals.html page; if the user chooses login then the users credentials will be checked prior to the page pick-goals.html being loaded-->  
  <button type="submit" class="logIn">Login</button>      
  <button onclick="location.href='signUp.html';" type="submit" class="signUP">Signup</button>
  </form>
</div>
</section>
  
</main>
        
<script src="index.js"></script>
</body>
</html>